cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CY

This paper discusses the security and privacy issues related to location-based social networks (LBSNs) and proposes an automated user location tracking system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of machine learning and data mining techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes the use of grid reference system and location classification, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the attacks on user privacy, which could also make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
